Photo by Awareness • Mindset • Success on September 10, 2021. May be an image of text that says '7 Ways to Improve Emotional Intelligence 1. Reflect on your emotions. This is where self-awareness begins. Το grow in emotional intelligence, think about your own emotions and how you typically react to negative situations. @AWARENESS_OF_SUCCESS'.

Photo by Awareness • Mindset • Success on September 10, 2021. May be an image of text that says '7 Ways to Improve Emotional Intelligence 2. Ask for perspective. Start getting input from others to understand how you come across in emotionally charged situations. @AWARENESS_OF_SUCCESS'.

Photo by Awareness • Mindset • Success on September 10, 2021. May be an image of text that says '7 Ways to Improve Emotional Intelligence 4. Pause for a moment. Stop and think before you act or speak. It's hard to do, but keep working at it, and it will become a habit. @AWARENESS_OF_SUCCESS'.

Photo by Awareness • Mindset • Success on September 10, 2021. May be an image of text that says '7 Ways to Improve Emotional Intelligence 5. Understand the "why." Try to understand the "why" behind another berson's feelings or emotions. This gives you compassion, perspective, and understanding. @AWARENESS_OF_SUCCESS'.

Photo by Awareness • Mindset • Success on September 10, 2021. May be an image of text that says '7 Ways to Improve Emotional Intelligence 6. Learn from criticism When we choose to learn from criticism rather than simply defend our behaviors, we can grow in emotional intelligence. @AWARENESS_OF_SUCCESS'.

Photo by Awareness • Mindset • Success on September 10, 2021. May be an image of text that says '7 Ways to Improve Emotional Intelligence 7. Practice practice. Becoming more emotionally intelligent won't happen overnight, but it can happen-with effort, patience, and a lot of practice @AWARENESS_OF_SUCCESS'.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Awareness • Mindset • Success on September 08, 2021. May be an image of text that says 'How to Improve Self-Discipline S @awareness_of_success'.

Photo by Awareness • Mindset • Success on September 08, 2021. May be an image of one or more people and text that says 'How to Improve Self-Discipline 1. Self- Self-discipline is different from discipline. When you say you're disciplined, you do what you need to do because someone else is watching you. But when you are self-disciplined, you do what you need to do even if you've only made your promise to yourself. @awareness_of_success'.

Photo by Awareness • Mindset • Success on September 08, 2021. May be an image of one or more people and text that says 'How to Improve Self-Discipline 2. Learn how to delay gratification. Many times it's easy to give in to our desire for comfort. But if you want to acnieve greater things, you have to learn how to create sacrifices and prioritize your goals. AS @awareness_of_success'.

Photo by Awareness • Mindset • Success on September 08, 2021. May be an image of text that says 'How to Improve Self-Discipline 3. Don't wait to get in the mood Here's the truth, you are never going to be in the mood 100% unless you decide that you will do something. Act on what you need to do. Don't give yourself enough time to reason or talk yourself out of the things that you ought to do. @awareness_of_success'.

Photo by Awareness • Mindset • Success on September 08, 2021. May be an image of text that says 'How to Improve Self-Discipline 4. Make it achievable The goals you set for yourself have to be realistic, yet challenging. Be careful not to set unachievable deadlines or targets because you will be setting yourself up to fail. When you've failed too many times, you might just get demotivated or even mess up your confidence. @awareness_of_success'.

Photo by Awareness • Mindset • Success on September 08, 2021. May be an image of one or more people and text that says 'How to Improve Self-Discipline 5. Create a routine Consistent actions towards your goals soon will transform into a habit. It's much better to do it one small step at a time than to try to do a lot and get stuck in the end. @awareness_of_success'.

Photo by Awareness • Mindset • Success on September 08, 2021. May be an image of one or more people and text that says 'How to Improve Self-Discipline 6. Think long term results Look ahead to around 3 to 5 years from now. Think about how your life will look like. Are the actions you're doing today directing you towards your desires? AS @awareness_of_success'.

Photo by Awareness • Mindset • Success on September 08, 2021. May be an image of text that says 'How to Improve Self-Discipline 7. Create accounability Be more accountable for your goals by letting other people know about them. Have somebody dared you to do something, and you did it just to save face even though you're so terrified or hated doing it? It's the same principle in action here but in a much healthier way. @awareness_of_success'.
Photo by Awareness • Mindset • Success on September 08, 2021. May be an image of one or more people and text that says 'Type "YES" below if you needed to hear this today! AS @awareness_of_success'.

Photo by Awareness • Mindset • Success on September 08, 2021. May be an image of one or more people and text that says 'DOUBLE TAP & SAVE THIS POST NOW AS A REMINDER! Help us spread the love, inspire and motivate others by sharing this post to your story & tagging us. Plus... you'll get a chance to be featured on our page! wareness_of_success'.

Photo by Awareness • Mindset • Success on September 08, 2021. May be an image of text that says 'My actual goals are to be so successful & independent that I can spoil myself, my family, and do what| love, and go where I want whenever I want. @AWARENESS_OF_SUCCESS'.
